pageToken.description: Optional. Page token received from a previous `ListWorkflowConfigs` call. Provide this to retrieve the subsequent page. When paginating, all other parameters provided to `ListWorkflowConfigs` must match the call that provided the page token.

parent.description: Required. The repository in which to list workflow configs. Must be in the format `projects/*/locations/*/repositories/*`.

list.description: Lists WorkflowConfigs in a given Repository.

parent.description: Required. The repository in which to create the workflow config. Must be in the format `projects/*/locations/*/repositories/*`.

workflowConfigId.description: Required. The ID to use for the workflow config, which will become the final component of the workflow config's resource name.

query.description: Returns WorkflowInvocationActions in a given WorkflowInvocation.

pageToken.description: Optional. Page token received from a previous `QueryWorkflowInvocationActions` call. Provide this to retrieve the subsequent page. When paginating, all other parameters provided to `QueryWorkflowInvocationActions` must match the call that provided the page token.

pageSize.description: Optional. Maximum number of workflow invocations to return. The server may return fewer items than requested. If unspecified, the server will pick an appropriate default.

pageSize.description: Optional. Maximum number of workflow invocations to return. The server may return fewer items than requested. If unspecified, the server will pick an appropriate default.

parent.description: Required. The parent resource of the WorkflowInvocation type. Must be in the format `projects/*/locations/*/repositories/*`.

filter.description: Optional. Filter for the returned list.

orderBy.description: Optional. This field only supports ordering by `name`. If unspecified, the server will choose the ordering. If specified, the default order is ascending for the `name` field.

name.description: Required. The workflow invocation resource's name.
